the doll... omg... just Why?? honestly, if you wanted a doll (for yourself, i mean, NOT to sell!) there's actually a really cute and cool Fashionista from Mattel that looks so much like Ro, it's startling. (Fashionista doll no.61 "Nice in Nautical") just fix the clothing to closer to her style, and Boom! your very own Ro doll.


the outfit one... coupled with the towel... holy cats! that was funny. Weird AF but Fun-Nee. XD
i think the round thing was actually what they call a "throw blanket". it's kind of a thing old ladies put over the back of their "sofas".
the rest of the stuff (cut out aside... will talk about that one last) is pretty cringey.


now that cut-out... i've actually seen a lot of youtubers with those. from Pewdie Pie (Felix?) to Mark to Séan (Jack).
nobody mentions that they didn't give them permission to make those. and they Do order them.
it's very confusing. i think whomever is doing it is getting mixed messages on the legal front. i am Not saying what they're doing is right OR legal. i'm just saying they're likely to come back with, "but everybody else is okay with it" as their supposed defense.
i really think you (Ro) should have a chat with the others and find out what's what on that one. i'm kind of wondering if you'll find out the they were Sort of given permission by YouTube to do this stuff. just something that came to my mind. admittedly, i have little faith in the people at YT Not doing something like that with out making sure it was kosher with the creators to do it. they aren't what i call, totally on the up-n-up to me. but then, i'm a suspicious old fart.
